tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: All parameters are within normal limits except for mildly decreased fasting glucose (64.9 mg/dL), which may indicate possible hypoglycemia; clinical correlation is recommended. Renal function, electrolytes, and HbA1c are unremarkable. No acute laboratory abnormalities detected.
